      "content_preview": "1.1 What Tara Balam means  Tara Balam literally means the strength or support obtained from the Nakshatra relationship between the native’s birth Moon and the Moon at the chosen muhurta. In electional astrology, the birth Moon is treated as the psychological and experiential anch"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch-1",
      "number": "1",
      "title": "Define the event precisely",
      "level": 1,
      "start_line": 622,
      "end_line": 625,
      "sections": [],
      "content_preview": "1. Define the event precisely  Is it marriage, house entry, travel, surgery, business launch, study, buying, worship, agriculture, legal filing or routine work? The purpose decides the rules.  2. Identify the principal native(s)  Record Janma Nakshatra, Janma Rasi, birth Moon pad"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch-2",
      "number": "2",
      "title": "Identify the principal native(s)",
      "level": 1,
      "start_line": 626,
      "end_line": 629,
      "sections": [],
      "content_preview": "2. Identify the principal native(s)  Record Janma Nakshatra, Janma Rasi, birth Moon pada, and whether multiple people must be evaluated.  3. Fix real-world constraints  Location, date range, ceremony duration, non-negotiable participants, daylight/night requirements and legal/pra"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch-3",
      "number": "3",
      "title": "Fix real-world constraints",
      "level": 1,
      "start_line": 630,
      "end_line": 633,
      "sections": [],
      "content_preview": "3. Fix real-world constraints  Location, date range, ceremony duration, non-negotiable participants, daylight/night requirements and legal/practical deadlines.  4. Remove obvious calendar exclusions  Reject impossible windows, eclipses, unsuitable sankramana zones, and known forb"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch-4",
      "number": "4",
      "title": "Remove obvious calendar exclusions",
      "level": 1,
      "start_line": 634,
      "end_line": 637,
      "sections": [],
      "content_preview": "4. Remove obvious calendar exclusions  Reject impossible windows, eclipses, unsuitable sankramana zones, and known forbidden periods in the chosen tradition.  5. Apply Panchanga Shuddhi  Check tithi, vara, nakshatra, yoga and karana for the activity. "
    },
    {
      "id": "ch-5",
      "number": "5",
      "title": "Apply Panchanga Shuddhi",
      "level": 1,
      "start_line": 638,
      "end_line": 641,
      "sections": [],
      "content_preview": "5. Apply Panchanga Shuddhi  Check tithi, vara, nakshatra, yoga and karana for the activity.  6. Apply Tara Balam  Classify the muhurta Moon Nakshatra from each principal Janma Nakshatra. Prefer remainders 2, 4, 6, 8, 0. "
    },
    {
      "id": "ch-6",
      "number": "6",
      "title": "Apply Tara Balam",
      "level": 1,
      "start_line": 642,
      "end_line": 645,
      "sections": [],
      "content_preview": "6. Apply Tara Balam  Classify the muhurta Moon Nakshatra from each principal Janma Nakshatra. Prefer remainders 2, 4, 6, 8, 0.  7. Apply Chandrabala  Check Moon sign from Janma Rasi, avoid 6/8/12 in stricter practice, and treat Chandra Ashtama carefully. "
    },
    {
      "id": "ch-7",
      "number": "7",
      "title": "Apply Chandrabala",
      "level": 1,
      "start_line": 646,
      "end_line": 649,
      "sections": [],
      "content_preview": "7. Apply Chandrabala  Check Moon sign from Janma Rasi, avoid 6/8/12 in stricter practice, and treat Chandra Ashtama carefully.  8. Inspect Paryaya and Pada nuances  For negative Tara, check if it is 1st, 2nd or 3rd Paryaya; inspect specific padas and 88th pada if high-stake. "
    },
    {
      "id": "ch-8",
      "number": "8",
      "title": "Inspect Paryaya and Pada nuances",
      "level": 1,
      "start_line": 650,
      "end_line": 653,
      "sections": [],
      "content_preview": "8. Inspect Paryaya and Pada nuances  For negative Tara, check if it is 1st, 2nd or 3rd Paryaya; inspect specific padas and 88th pada if high-stake.  9. Test special warnings  Check Vainasika 22nd, restricted 27th, Janma group cautions, activity-specific Nakshatra bans. "
    },
    {
      "id": "ch-9",
      "number": "9",
      "title": "Test special warnings",
      "level": 1,
      "start_line": 654,
      "end_line": 657,
      "sections": [],
      "content_preview": "9. Test special warnings  Check Vainasika 22nd, restricted 27th, Janma group cautions, activity-specific Nakshatra bans.  10. Build the election chart  Choose a strong Lagna; avoid malefics in Lagna, Karthari, Moon affliction, weak Lagna lord or afflicted event significator. "
    },
    {
      "id": "ch-10",
      "number": "10",
      "title": "Build the election chart",
      "level": 1,
      "start_line": 658,
      "end_line": 661,
      "sections": [],
      "content_preview": "10. Build the election chart  Choose a strong Lagna; avoid malefics in Lagna, Karthari, Moon affliction, weak Lagna lord or afflicted event significator.  11. Seek strengthening yogas  Prefer benefics in kendras/trikonas, strong Lagna lord, strong relevant house lord, and favorab"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch-11",
      "number": "11",
      "title": "Seek strengthening yogas",
      "level": 1,
      "start_line": 662,
      "end_line": 665,
      "sections": [],
      "content_preview": "11. Seek strengthening yogas  Prefer benefics in kendras/trikonas, strong Lagna lord, strong relevant house lord, and favorable special yogas.  12. Make the final judgment  Use A/B/C/D rating. If a defect is relevant to the activity and cannot be neutralized, reject or downgrade."
    },
