    {
      "id": "ch-1",
      "number": "1",
      "title": "Read the slot",
      "level": 1,
      "start_line": 788,
      "end_line": 791,
      "sections": [],
      "content_preview": "1. Read the slot  Note start time, end time and named muhurta division.  2. Identify the Moon Nakshatra  Use location-specific Panchanga. If a Nakshatra changes inside the slot, split the slot. "
    },
    {
      "id": "ch-2",
      "number": "2",
      "title": "Identify the Moon Nakshatra",
      "level": 1,
      "start_line": 792,
      "end_line": 795,
      "sections": [],
      "content_preview": "2. Identify the Moon Nakshatra  Use location-specific Panchanga. If a Nakshatra changes inside the slot, split the slot.  3. Classify Tara  Count from the person’s Janma Nakshatra to the active Moon Nakshatra. "
    },
    {
      "id": "ch-3",
      "number": "3",
      "title": "Classify Tara",
      "level": 1,
      "start_line": 796,
      "end_line": 799,
      "sections": [],
      "content_preview": "3. Classify Tara  Count from the person’s Janma Nakshatra to the active Moon Nakshatra.  4. Apply activity filter  Check whether the Tara’s nature supports the actual event. "
    },
    {
      "id": "ch-4",
      "number": "4",
      "title": "Apply activity filter",
      "level": 1,
      "start_line": 800,
      "end_line": 803,
      "sections": [],
      "content_preview": "4. Apply activity filter  Check whether the Tara’s nature supports the actual event.  5. Check special exceptions  Paryaya, Pada, Vainasika, 27th, Janma group, 88th Pada. "
    },
    {
      "id": "ch-5",
      "number": "5",
      "title": "Check special exceptions",
      "level": 1,
      "start_line": 804,
      "end_line": 807,
      "sections": [],
      "content_preview": "5. Check special exceptions  Paryaya, Pada, Vainasika, 27th, Janma group, 88th Pada.  6. Combine with named muhurta quality  A good Tara does not automatically override a named inauspicious muhurta division; use both layers. "
    },
    {
      "id": "ch-6",
      "number": "6",
      "title": "Combine with named muhurta quality",
      "level": 1,
      "start_line": 808,
      "end_line": 811,
      "sections": [],
      "content_preview": "6. Combine with named muhurta quality  A good Tara does not automatically override a named inauspicious muhurta division; use both layers.  7. Select best segment  Prefer the sub-slot with favorable Tara, clean Panchanga, good Chandrabala and strongest Lagna. "
    },
    {
      "id": "ch-7",
      "number": "7",
      "title": "Select best segment",
      "level": 1,
      "start_line": 812,
      "end_line": 1904,
      "sections": [],
      "content_preview": "7. Select best segment  Prefer the sub-slot with favorable Tara, clean Panchanga, good Chandrabala and strongest Lagna.  Important for your earlier 2-ghati tables  The “corresponding Nakshatra” beside each 2-ghati interval is the input for Tara Balam. "
